Generate a segment of longitudinal medical events for this synthetic patient.

Overall patient description: {{recipe.description}}

Segment-specific description: {{segment.description}}

* your output should be a JSON object: {"records": {time: [[code_system, code_desc] or [code_system, code_desc, numeric_value, unit], ...], ...}}
* generate events sequentially by time for this segment only. these should be specific events that would actually be coded in a typical {% if record_type == 'claims' %} claims record {% else %} electronic health record {% endif %}
* time: {% if record_type in ['claims', 'ehr-outpatient'] %}use strict date precision (YYYY-MM-DD){% else %}use strict datetime precision (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM){% endif %}. If the descriptions have any strict constraints about dates, make sure to heed them. 
* code_system: the vocabulary system for this code (must be one of: {{ allowed_code_systems | join(', ') }})
* code_desc: brief textual description of the measurement/event (not the code itself). focus on concepts, diagnoses, observations, procedures, prescriptions, etc. that would actually appear in a health record.
* for non-numeric events: output [code_system, code_desc]
* for numeric events: output [code_system, code_desc, numeric_value, unit] (unit is required when numeric_value is present). {% if loinc_allowed and not (record_type == 'claims') %}loinc codes should always be accompanied by measurements in this way.{% endif %}

* the segment should span from {{start_date}} to {{end_date}}
* approximately {{segment.num_times * segment.avg_codes_per_time}} total events for this segment (CRUCIAL! do *not* generate fewer)
* approximately {{segment.num_times}} time points
* {{segment.avg_codes_per_time}} codes per time point, on average

